\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.5}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Metadata Annotation:} Each patient file is labelled with the patient's name. \textbf  {Chunking:} ``Recursive Character Text Splitter`` splits the text into chunks of 550 characters with 50-character overlap. \textbf  {Chunk Prefixing:} The patient's name and AMKA is appended to each chunk in order to make it identifiable and improve retrieval accuracy. \textbf  {Embedding model:} The embedding model ``paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2`` encodes each chunk and stores it into the Chroma vector database, together with the patient's name annotation as its metadata.}}{70}{figure.caption.70}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:SystemAChunkingEmbeddingChroma}{{4.5}{70}{\textbf {Metadata Annotation:} Each patient file is labelled with the patient's name. \textbf {Chunking:} ``Recursive Character Text Splitter`` splits the text into chunks of 550 characters with 50-character overlap. \textbf {Chunk Prefixing:} The patient's name and AMKA is appended to each chunk in order to make it identifiable and improve retrieval accuracy. \textbf {Embedding model:} The embedding model ``paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2`` encodes each chunk and stores it into the Chroma vector database, together with the patient's name annotation as its metadata}{figure.caption.70}{}}
